* partition connection caching
    * determine partition ordering
        - upperbound

    * dynamic ordering
        - upperbound
        - d-separation
        - decendent independence
    * static ordering
        - upperbound
        - d-separation
        - decendent independence
        - equivalence after conditioning

* traversal optimization
    * local
        - pick new root within and leaf
            - d-separation
            - decendent independence
            - uninitialized subfunctions return 1, at root of each BN variable
                - summing over all variable values adds to 1
                - requires non-interleaved ordering

    * global
        - only applicable to partitions
        - see optimization for partition caching

